                            <comment id="13295436" author="lakshman" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 03:22:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thinking of following approach. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;grant, revoke, getUserPermissions, checkPermissions - All these apis needs to be authorized against CQ/CF/table/global admin permissions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Append - WRITE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any corrections required?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13296030" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 16 Jun 2012 00:11:42 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Append operation also has no authorization check.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Append was added after initial drop, so didn&apos;t get coverage. Agree WRITE is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13396984" author="lakshman" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 18:59:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On closure look, checkPermissions need not be corrected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13396989" author="lakshman" created="Tue, 19 Jun 2012 19:05:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch includes ACL corrections for grant, revoke, getUserPermissions and Append.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
